+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NoMTWZ24zPqN6zVLCA7jnT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NpJWMAB3E6o8EKGmdfij5w","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-reactive-spreadsheet.md","content":"# Reactive Spreadsheet Engine Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a TypeScript spreadsheet engine with formula parsing, reactive dependency tracking, and circular reference detection.\n\n**Architecture:** The engine has 4 layers: (1) cell reference parsing, (2) formula tokenizer/parser producing an AST, (3) formula evaluator that walks the AST, (4) dependency graph for reactive updates. The `Spreadsheet` class ties them together, storing raw values and recomputing dependents on change.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Vitest for tests, no runtime dependencies.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Cell Reference Utilities\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/cell-utils.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.ts` (stub)\n- Test: `src/__tests__/cell-utils.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/__tests__/cell-utils.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { parseCellRef, cellRefToString, columnToNumber, numberToColumn, expandRange } from '../cell-utils';\n\ndescribe('cell-utils', () => {\n  describe('columnToNumber', () => {\n    it('converts single letters', () => {\n      expect(columnToNumber('A')).toBe(1);\n      expect(columnToNumber('Z')).toBe(26);\n    });\n    it('converts multi-letter columns', () => {\n      expect(columnToNumber('AA')).toBe(27);\n      expect(columnToNumber('AZ')).toBe(52);\n      expect(columnToNumber('BA')).toBe(53);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('numberToColumn', () => {\n    it('converts numbers to column letters', () => {\n      expect(numberToColumn(1)).toBe('A');\n      expect(numberToColumn(26)).toBe('Z');\n      expect(numberToColumn(27)).toBe('AA');\n      expect(numberToColumn(52)).toBe('AZ');\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('parseCellRef', () => {\n    it('parses simple refs', () => {\n      expect(parseCellRef('A1')).toEqual({ col: 1, row: 1 });\n      expect(parseCellRef('B2')).toEqual({ col: 2, row: 2 });\n      expect(parseCellRef('Z100')).toEqual({ col: 26, row: 100 });\n    });\n    it('parses multi-letter columns', () => {\n      expect(parseCellRef('AA1')).toEqual({ col: 27, row: 1 });\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('cellRefToString', () => {\n    it('converts back to string', () => {\n      expect(cellRefToString({ col: 1, row: 1 })).toBe('A1');\n      expect(cellRefToString({ col: 27, row: 1 })).toBe('AA1');\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('expandRange', () => {\n    it('expands column range', () => {\n      expect(expandRange('A1', 'A3')).toEqual(['A1', 'A2', 'A3']);\n    });\n    it('expands row range', () => {\n      expect(expandRange('A1', 'C1')).toEqual(['A1', 'B1', 'C1']);\n    });\n    it('expands block range', () => {\n      const result = expandRange('A1', 'B2');\n      expect(result).toEqual(['A1', 'A2', 'B1', 'B2']);\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/cell-utils.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL — modules not found\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```typescript\n// src/cell-utils.ts\nexport interface CellRef {\n  col: number;\n  row: number;\n}\n\nexport function columnToNumber(col: string): number {\n  let result = 0;\n  for (let i = 0; i < col.length; i++) {\n    result = result * 26 + (col.charCodeAt(i) - 64);\n  }\n  return result;\n}\n\nexport function numberToColumn(num: number): string {\n  let result = '';\n  while (num > 0) {\n    num--;\n    result = String.fromCharCode(65 + (num % 26)) + result;\n    num = Math.floor(num / 26);\n  }\n  return result;\n}\n\nexport function parseCellRef(ref: string): CellRef {\n  const match = ref.match(/^([A-Z]+)(\\d+)$/);\n  if (!match) throw new Error(`Invalid cell reference: ${ref}`);\n  return { col: columnToNumber(match[1]), row: parseInt(match[2], 10) };\n}\n\nexport function cellRefToString(ref: CellRef): string {\n  return numberToColumn(ref.col) + ref.row;\n}\n\nexport function expandRange(start: string, end: string): string[] {\n  const s = parseCellRef(start);\n  const e = parseCellRef(end);\n  const cells: string[] = [];\n  for (let c = s.col; c <= e.col; c++) {\n    for (let r = s.row; r <= e.row; r++) {\n      cells.push(cellRefToString({ col: c, row: r }));\n    }\n  }\n  return cells;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/cell-utils.test.ts`\nExpected: PASS\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Formula Tokenizer\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tokenizer.ts`\n- Test: `src/__tests__/tokenizer.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\n```typescript\n// src/__tests__/tokenizer.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { tokenize, TokenType } from '../tokenizer';\n\ndescribe('tokenizer', () => {\n  it('tokenizes numbers', () => {\n    const tokens = tokenize('42');\n    expect(tokens).toEqual([{ type: TokenType.Number, value: '42' }]);\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes decimals', () => {\n    const tokens = tokenize('3.14');\n    expect(tokens).toEqual([{ type: TokenType.Number, value: '3.14' }]);\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes cell references', () => {\n    const tokens = tokenize('A1');\n    expect(tokens).toEqual([{ type: TokenType.CellRef, value: 'A1' }]);\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes function names', () => {\n    const tokens = tokenize('SUM');\n    expect(tokens).toEqual([{ type: TokenType.Function, value: 'SUM' }]);\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes arithmetic', () => {\n    const tokens = tokenize('A1+B1');\n    expect(tokens).toEqual([\n      { type: TokenType.CellRef, value: 'A1' },\n      { type: TokenType.Operator, value: '+' },\n      { type: TokenType.CellRef, value: 'B1' },\n    ]);\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes comparison operators', () => {\n    expect(tokenize('A1>=10')).toContainEqual({ type: TokenType.Operator, value: '>=' });\n    expect(tokenize('A1<>B1')).toContainEqual({ type: TokenType.Operator, value: '<>' });\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes parentheses and commas', () => {\n    const tokens = tokenize('SUM(A1:A3)');\n    expect(tokens.map(t => t.type)).toEqual([\n      TokenType.Function, TokenType.LParen, TokenType.CellRef,\n      TokenType.Colon, TokenType.CellRef, TokenType.RParen,\n    ]);\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes string literals', () => {\n    const tokens = tokenize('\"hello\"');\n    expect(tokens).toEqual([{ type: TokenType.String, value: 'hello' }]);\n  });\n\n  it('tokenizes booleans', () => {\n    expect(tokenize('true')).toEqual([{ type: TokenType.Boolean, value: 'true' }]);\n    expect(tokenize('false')).toEqual([{ type: TokenType.Boolean, value: 'false' }]);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify fail**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/tokenizer.test.ts`\n\n**Step 3: Write implementation**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tokenizer.ts\nexport enum TokenType {\n  Number = 'Number',\n  String = 'String',\n  Boolean = 'Boolean',\n  CellRef = 'CellRef',\n  Function = 'Function',\n  Operator = 'Operator',\n  LParen = 'LParen',\n  RParen = 'RParen',\n  Comma = 'Comma',\n  Colon = 'Colon',\n}\n\nexport interface Token {\n  type: TokenType;\n  value: string;\n}\n\nconst FUNCTIONS = new Set(['SUM', 'AVERAGE', 'MIN', 'MAX', 'COUNT', 'IF']);\n\nexport function tokenize(input: string): Token[] {\n  const tokens: Token[] = [];\n  let i = 0;\n\n  while (i < input.length) {\n    if (input[i] === ' ') { i++; continue; }\n\n    // String literals\n    if (input[i] === '\"') {\n      let str = '';\n      i++;\n      while (i < input.length && input[i] !== '\"') {\n        str += input[i++];\n      }\n      i++; // skip closing quote\n      tokens.push({ type: TokenType.String, value: str });\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Numbers\n    if (/\\d/.test(input[i])) {\n      let num = '';\n      while (i < input.length && /[\\d.]/.test(input[i])) {\n        num += input[i++];\n      }\n      tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Number, value: num });\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Letters: cell refs, function names, booleans\n    if (/[A-Za-z]/.test(input[i])) {\n      let word = '';\n      while (i < input.length && /[A-Za-z0-9]/.test(input[i])) {\n        word += input[i++];\n      }\n      const upper = word.toUpperCase();\n      if (upper === 'TRUE' || upper === 'FALSE') {\n        tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Boolean, value: upper.toLowerCase() });\n      } else if (FUNCTIONS.has(upper) && i < input.length && input[i] === '(') {\n        tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Function, value: upper });\n      } else if (/^[A-Z]+\\d+$/.test(upper)) {\n        tokens.push({ type: TokenType.CellRef, value: upper });\n      } else if (FUNCTIONS.has(upper)) {\n        tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Function, value: upper });\n      } else {\n        throw new Error(`Unknown identifier: ${word}`);\n      }\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Two-char operators\n    if (i + 1 < input.length) {\n      const two = input[i] + input[i + 1];\n      if (['>=', '<=', '<>'].includes(two)) {\n        tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Operator, value: two });\n        i += 2;\n        continue;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Single-char tokens\n    const ch = input[i];\n    if ('+-*/'.includes(ch) || ch === '>' || ch === '<' || ch === '=') {\n      tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Operator, value: ch });\n    } else if (ch === '(') {\n      tokens.push({ type: TokenType.LParen, value: ch });\n    } else if (ch === ')') {\n      tokens.push({ type: TokenType.RParen, value: ch });\n    } else if (ch === ',') {\n      tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Comma, value: ch });\n    } else if (ch === ':') {\n      tokens.push({ type: TokenType.Colon, value: ch });\n    } else {\n      throw new Error(`Unexpected character: ${ch}`);\n    }\n    i++;\n  }\n\n  return tokens;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify pass**\n\nRun: `npx vitest run src/__tests__/tokenizer.test.ts`\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Formula Parser (AST)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/parser.ts`\n- Test: `src/__tests__/parser.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\nTest that the parser produces correct AST nodes for expressions like `A1+B1*2`, `SUM(A1:A3)`, `IF(A1>0,\"yes\",\"no\")`, and `(A1+B1)*2`.\n\n**Step 2: Write implementation**\n\nThe parser uses recursive descent with proper operator precedence:\n- Level 1 (lowest): Comparison operators (`>`, `<`, `>=`, `<=`, `=`, `<>`)\n- Level 2: Addition/subtraction (`+`, `-`)\n- Level 3: Multiplication/division (`*`, `/`)\n- Level 4 (highest): Unary minus, atoms (numbers, strings, booleans, cell refs, function calls, parenthesized expressions)\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Formula Evaluator\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/evaluator.ts`\n- Test: `src/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts`\n\nWalks the AST and evaluates. Cell references are resolved via a callback `(ref: string) => CellValue`. Range functions aggregate values using `expandRange`.\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Spreadsheet Class with Dependency Graph\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/spreadsheet.ts`\n- Modify: `src/index.ts` (re-export)\n- Test: `src/__tests__/spreadsheet.test.ts`\n\nThe Spreadsheet class:\n- Stores raw values in a `Map<string, string | number | boolean>`\n- Maintains a dependency graph: `dependents` (who depends on me) and `dependencies` (who do I depend on)\n- On `set()`: parse formula if starts with `=`, extract cell refs, update dep graph, check for cycles (DFS), evaluate, then topological-sort dependents and recompute\n- `get()` returns computed value, `getDisplay()` returns string representation\n- Circular reference detection via DFS from the cell being set through dependents\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Integration Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Test: `src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n\nCover the full API: reactive updates, chained formulas, circular reference errors, all built-in functions, block ranges, display formatting.\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Build & Lint\n\nRun: `npm run build && npm run lint && npx vitest run`\nFix any issues.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":114,"cache_read_input_tokens":20728,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":114},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1537049a-5913-4eec-8ffe-ad8cd36ef3f5","uuid":"1427f312-5132-4024-9d84-00d34e7e735f"}
