+### Task 3: Formula Parser (AST)
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/parser.ts`
+- Test: `src/__tests__/parser.test.ts`
+
+**Step 1: Write the failing tests**
+
+Test that the parser produces correct AST nodes for expressions like `A1+B1*2`, `SUM(A1:A3)`, `IF(A1>0,"yes","no")`, and `(A1+B1)*2`.
+
+**Step 2: Write implementation**
+
+The parser uses recursive descent with proper operator precedence:
+- Level 1 (lowest): Comparison operators (`>`, `<`, `>=`, `<=`, `=`, `<>`)
+- Level 2: Addition/subtraction (`+`, `-`)
+- Level 3: Multiplication/division (`*`, `/`)
+- Level 4 (highest): Unary minus, atoms (numbers, strings, booleans, cell refs, function calls, parenthesized expressions)
+
+---
+
+### Task 4: Formula Evaluator
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/evaluator.ts`
+- Test: `src/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts`
+
+Walks the AST and evaluates. Cell references are resolved via a callback `(ref: string) => CellValue`. Range functions aggregate values using `expandRange`.
+
+---
+
+### Task 5: Spreadsheet Class with Dependency Graph
+
+**Files:**
+- Create: `src/spreadsheet.ts`
+- Modify: `src/index.ts` (re-export)
+- Test: `src/__tests__/spreadsheet.test.ts`
+
+The Spreadsheet class:
+- Stores raw values in a `Map<string, string | number | boolean>`
+- Maintains a dependency graph: `dependents` (who depends on me) and `dependencies` (who do I depend on)
+- On `set()`: parse formula if starts with `=`, extract cell refs, update dep graph, check for cycles (DFS), evaluate, then topological-sort dependents and recompute
+- `get()` returns computed value, `getDisplay()` returns string representation
+- Circular reference detection via DFS from the cell being set through dependents
+
+---
+
+### Task 6: Integration Tests
+
+**Files:**
+- Test: `src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`
+
+Cover the full API: reactive updates, chained formulas, circular reference errors, all built-in functions, block ranges, display formatting.
+
+---
+
+### Task 7: Build & Lint
+
+Run: `npm run build && npm run lint && npx vitest run`
+Fix any issues.
